# Python Cheat Sheet (Beginner Level)

## Introduction
Python is a beginner-friendly programming language that is easy to read and understand. 
It is widely used by students to learn basic programming concepts and problem-solving skills.

## Key Concepts
- Simple and readable syntax
- Uses indentation instead of braces
- Dynamically typed language
- Open-source and free to use

## Simple Syntax Examples
Variables  
x = 10  
name = "Python"

Data Types  
a = 5  
b = 2.5  
c = "Hello"

Conditional Statement  
if a > 3:
    print("Greater than 3")

Loop  
for i in range(3):
    print(i)

List  
numbers = [1, 2, 3]

## Real-Life or Business Use Case
In economics and business studies, Python is used to perform simple calculations, understand logical conditions, and work with basic data efficiently.

## Advantages
- Very easy for beginners to learn
- Requires fewer lines of code
- Large community support
- Useful in academics and business fields

## Limitations
- Slower execution speed compared to some languages
- Not suitable for mobile app development
- High memory usage in some cases

## Summary
A Python cheat sheet acts as a quick reference guide for beginners. 
It helps students revise syntax easily and supports effective learning of programming fundamentals.
